The Tembisa Tertiary Hospital. Google Earth JOHANNESBURG - Tembisa Hospital CEO, Lekopane Mogaladi, has been suspended following a report into the death of Shonisani Lethole at the facility last year. The businessman died after going for several days without eating and receiving sub-standard care. READ: Sama calls for healthcare reforms Health Ombudsman, Malegapuru Makgoba, found the hospital guilty of gross negligence. Makgoba says Lethole's death was preventable.